		"description": {
			"value": "<p>An amphibious creature has adapted to live both on land and in water.</p><ul><li>Add the amphibious trait. If the creature has the aquatic trait, remove it.</li><li>Add Athletics with a modifier equal to the creature's highest skill modifier.</li><li>If the creature doesn't have a swim Speed, add a swim Speed equal to half its land Speed (minimum 15 feet).</li><li>If the creature doesn't have a land Speed, add a land Speed equal to half its swim Speed (minimum 15 feet).</li><li><p>Add the following abilities:</p></li><li><p>@UUID[Compendium.pf2e.bestiary-ability-glossary-srd.Item.fFu2sZz4KB01fVRc]{Low-light Vision}</p></li><li><p>@UUID[Compendium.sundry.sundry-pf2e-templates.Item.CZMGNRSelThdwnKS]</p></li></ul>",
			"gm": "<p><strong>Note</strong> Calculation to get the land speed based on swim speed will run into issues on creatures with multiple alternative movement types</p>"
		},
